cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.DS 

The paper presents a new loss function for deep learning classification tasks and evaluates it on image datasets. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.CV (Computer Vision). Additionally, the paper discusses the properties of the loss function and its comparison to other robust losses, indicating a focus on theoretical aspects, which could place it in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of deep learning also suggests a possible fit for cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the evaluation of the loss function on datasets with label noise could also place it in cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
